items.name: RPGGriffon
items.description:
This is a LoRA for creating GRIFFONS for medieval rpgs. I am going to revisit this one as it's very ornery, but there are some good griffons. I find I've had to insert ((four paws)) at times to get it from being a biped depending on the prompt even though the training images all showed 4 paws/talons. Anyhow, there are some good images present. I did find that popping up sampling and the denoising on the upscaler did assist with retaining more of the look of the training images (not surprisingly I guess). That being said, some of the simple prompts work pretty well (e.g.; <lora:RPGGriffon:1> griffon:1.3, mountains, 8k, intricate details, depth of field, cinematic,)

The images were created with hires.fx x2, denoising 0.5, 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler

items.name: Demoscene Dreams - a retro riot in 16 colours
items.description:
The demoscene is a culture of coders, artists, and musicians who push their selected (usually retro) computer hardware to its limit creating music and videos to demonstrate its capabilities. This model has been trained on stills from the legendary 1992 demo State of the Art created by Norwegian collective Spaceballs. Check out the video and marvel that it was made for the Amiga 500, a computer with 1 megabyte of RAM and a 0.007 GHz processor.

Used at higher strengths, this LoRA will silhouette an image's subject behind a low-res layer of colours and lines. Combined with ControlNet, the effect can be directed at a composition's background, or target on particular textures and materials. At lower strengths, the effect is best described as "rainbow cyberpunk".

Two versions of this model are available: one trained against the base SD1.5 model, and one trained against a specialised cartoon-style checkpoint. The former will work well with base SD1.5 and photorealistic checkpoints, the latter will work better for Western animation and anime style checkpoints.

items.name: AstreaPixie Radiance
items.description:
First release of finetuned model in work for the last months. It aims at anime feeling with vibrant color, which gave me idea to give the name Radiance to the model.

Recommended Settings

- Clip skip: 2
- CFG scale: 8
- Sampler: DPM++ SDE and DPM++ 2m Karras
- Sampling Steps : 20-30
- Upscaler (Hires. fix): 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G  
- Hires steps: 10-15  Denoising strength: 0.35  Upscale by: 1.5+

Using Adetailer

- Main UI > Extensions > Install from URL
    This mainly fixes problems with faces and eyes. Do not use for hands.
    This can be enable and nothing else to do to works.

Why is my results different from yours?

  • Enable quantization in K samplers in your settings

  • Keep your prompts simple and correct

    • Tag auto complete extension to help you with your tags

    • Neg embedding have a great impact on the output of a model

    • Depending on the one you are using, results will be different.

    • I mainly use fitCorder embeddings for negative :)

You can support me on Ko-Fi and Patreon

items.name: Camila Vallejo
items.description:
Camila Vallejo Dowling (b. 1988) is a leftist Chilean politician who is currently the Minister Secretary General of Government — the government's chief spokesperson. She is a member of the Communist Party of Chile; her parents, also communists, were involved in the resistance to right-wing dictator Augusto Pinochet.

She gained global attention as a 23-year-old college student when, as head of the nation's largest student union, and led the Chilean student protests of 2011, which included the occupation of more than 100 schools and demonstrations of up to 600,000 people. The New York Times labeled her "the world's most glamorous revolutionary" and The Guardian's readers voted her Person of the Year. She was elected to Chile's Congress, where she served eight years, before joining the new leftist government of 35-year-old Gabriel Boric, another former student leader, in 2022.

This embedding is based on 30 images, cooked for a total of 300 steps on base SD1.5 — 16 vectors per token, a 0.004 learning rate, a batch size of 6, and 5 gradient steps.

items.name: Mikami Reiko (from Another)
items.description:
This was a rather complex LoRA I had to do and this is in part due to major spoilers revolving around Mikami Reiko.

To save on a lot of plot explanations (and to just explain why there's three models of her), one of these is the twist that she moonlights as a teacher at the school where the story is set. As such, there's three LoRAs for her: Her as just Reiko, her as just the teacher, and then, since her Teacher LoRA seemed rather stiff (and lowering the steps only seemed to reduce her details but after further comparisons, I think it might be okay enough to upload as a fourth model), I decided to merge the two into one LoRA as well, so you got four LoRAs in one character!

items.name: doaxvv_nagisa 渚 大色狗
items.description:
v1

  1. This model was trained on screenshots taken from within the game. It exhibits high levels of similarity and generalization. To enhance the expressiveness and liveliness of the generated characters, it is recommended to use emotional and action descriptors in the prompt. Furthermore, descriptions from different perspectives might produce surprising results.

    这是通过在游戏内截图训练出的模型，模型相似度和泛化性都非常之高，建议在prompt中多使用情绪和动作描述以提高表情和动作的生动性，同时不同视角的描述或许也会有惊喜。

  2. In order to maximize the authenticity of the characters, after testing more than a dozen underlying models, it was surprisingly found that the GhostMix mixed model yielded the best results. Consequently, this model was selected for training.

    为了最大化角色的还原程度，并且在试过了十几个底层模型之后，很奇妙的，我发现ghostmix这个混合模型效果居然最好，因此我决定采用这个模型进行训练。

  3. It is recommended to use a weight between 0.3 and 0.8 for image generation.

    建议使用0.3-0.8的权重进行图像生成

  4. The more complex the prompts are, the less likely the image is to collapse

    提示词越复杂，图像越不容易崩坏

v2

New version v2 is released!

The training iterations have been increased and the base model has been replaced to enhance generalization and reconstruction accuracy.Better results can also be achieved with fewer prompts.

增加了训练次数，更换了底模，使其泛化性和还原性更好，即使提示词很少，也能出现较好的效果

LoRA trained to generate a character holding an open towel. Nudity is optional ;)

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: Plutia/Iris Heart - Hyperdimension Neptunia Character LoRA
items.description:
About

Another LoRA of a mostly obscure character but she's probably one of my all time favourites so I just had to. You can use any weight you'd like, I've had a lot of success just leaving it at 1.

LoRA contains trigger words for both her forms, Plutia and Iris Heart along with trigger words for their outfits. The outfit ones just make it easier for their outfits to appear since I had a lot of images of them in the dataset without their normal outfit, so make sure to use both if you want the outfit consistently.

I prefer version B personally but all of them generate slightly different images on the same seeds, download whichever you like the look of.

Preview image generation parameters should all be in the images as per usual (Feel like that should be standard but just my opinion). She looks sad or angry in all my previews because I forgot to put in an expression tag.

Finally, the generation parameters might look weird or different, I use the SD Next fork of A1111 created by Vladmandic, so that's why, it's pretty easy to figure out what the generation parameters should be for the images though.

Training

I did this one a little differently, I used the Prodigy optimizer in Kohya ss and used a decay weight of 0.4/0.6, there are 3 different models available to download, each is just a different epoch. I don't think there's a big quality difference between the three but look at the images and decide for yourself, all of them will be using the same seed and generation parameters.
